programme.title: Border Security - Australia's Front Line
programme.desc: A lively man from the US arrives on a tourist visa, but Immigration believes he may be here to work illegally. And despite his claim of a clean criminal record, officers findings prove otherwise. A shipment from Hong Kong ostensibly containing three standard household doors provokes officers' interests when one of the doors is heavier than the others. An x-ray shows there may be organic matter concealed inside. Then two men from the Philippines arrive for a holiday after spending time working in Papua New Guinea, but Customs and Border Protection officers are concerned about their last minute flight-changes and lack of knowledge about what to see and do in Brisbane. Narrated by GRANT BOWLER.
